{"type":"message","id":"f6137587","parentId":"d3b616a8","timestamp":"2026-03-14T15:51:09.804Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The web_search is failing. Let me try using the process tool to run a command. Looking at the process tool more carefully, I need to check what actions are available. The description says \"Manage running exec sessions: list, poll, log, write, send-keys, submit, paste, kill.\"\n\nIt seems like I need to first create a session somehow. But there's no \"create\" or \"spawn\" action listed. Let me try using \"exec\" as the action since that's commonly used.\n\nActually, looking at the error message when I tried \"exec\", it said \"sessionId is required for this action.\" This suggests that sessions need to be created first through some other means.\n\nLet me try a different approach - maybe I can use the process tool with an action that creates a session. Let me check if there's a way to do this.\n\nActually, looking at the tool definition again more carefully:\n- action is required\n- sessionId is required for actions \"other than list\"\n\nSo \"list\" doesn't need a sessionId, but other actions do. This suggests sessions are created implicitly somehow. Let me try using \"submit\" action which might create a session.\n\nWait, I should try running the command differently. Let me try using the process tool with a simpler approach - maybe I need to just try to execute and it will create a session.\n\nActually, let me try using web_fetch to get information from a known URL about OpenAI, since web_search is failing.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4b6bdb24f858464a929a03f1","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://openai.com","maxChars":5000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}}